<title>USA: Microsoft files to offer $862.5 mln shares.</title>
<headline>Microsoft files to offer $862.5 mln shares.</headline>
<dateline>WASHINGTON 1996-12-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Microsoft Corp filed Monday with the Securities and Exchange Commission for permission to sell up to $862.5 million worth of preferred shares.</p>
<p>The series A preferred shares are convertible, exchangeable, and principal-protected, the Redmond, Wash.,-based company said.</p>
<p>They are exchangeable for the company's convertible subordinated notes due 1999, it added.</p>
